    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_1c03032__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow can be divided into seven steps... (1) Data input... Alternatively, a RAMClustR R object containing deconvolved pseudo-MS/MS spectra for the features can also be used as data input. Positive and negative ionization modes for the same chromatography are analyzed separately, to make effective use of mode-specific reference libraries.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes using RAMClustR objects and mode-specific libraries (positive/negative), but does not name a specific function called 'annotateRC'. The paper describes the workflow generically and mentions RAMClustR objects as input, but the specific function name 'annotateRC' is not found in passages. The workflow does support RAMClustR objects and lipid libraries in positive mode.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reproduce the lipid annotation results for six ESI+ features using annotateRC with LipidPos libraries",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:39:19.727175+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_1c03032__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A random selection of 100 LC\u2013MS AIF chromatograms from both Lipid+ and Lipid\u2013 as well as HILIC+ datasets from the MESA cohort was processed in R using XCMS version 3.4.4 and RAMClustR package to obtain pseudo-MS/MS spectra (dataset-wide reconstruction)... Automated annotations were obtained for manually annotated features in the MESA and validation datasets. The automated annotations were obtained separately using the lipid and nonlipid metabolite libraries and the results were combined.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms use of XCMS and RAMClustR objects with lipid libraries in positive mode, but does not reference a specific function 'annotateRC' or test on exactly 'six features' or 'three out of six' success rate. The workflow is demonstrated on 599 manually annotated features, not six.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Does the annotateRC function successfully annotate three out of six features from the targetTable.csv using xcmsSet and RAMClustR objects with LipidPos libraries?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:39:19.727175+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_1c03032__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we propose a new workflow for the annotation of lipidomics and metabolomics LC\u2013MS AIF datasets... The workflow has been implemented as an open-source R package MetaboAnnotatoR, providing tools for automated annotation, reporting, and visualization.",
      "asbval:note": "MetaboAnnotatoR is the primary tool developed and described in the paper.",
