      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_1c03032__task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For each target feature, a list of the candidates ranked by score is produced, which includes the metabolite name, m/z matched, m/z error (ppm), the number of matched fragments, and score. Additionally, a list containing all rank 1 annotations is produced for quick result inspection.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms that MetaboAnnotatoR produces ranked candidate tables with metabolite names, scores, and rank positions. However, the specific metabolite identities (LPC(14:0) as rank 1, PC(14:0) species at lower ranks) for feature 468.309 m/z are not explicitly stated in the passages. Figure 2C is referenced as showing a ranked candidate table for this feature, but the actual metabolite names in that table are not transcribed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Ranked candidate annotation table for feature 3, including metabolite names, annotation scores, and rank positions, with LPC(14:0) as rank 1 and PC(14:0)-containing species at lower ranks",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:39:43.532516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_1c03032__task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we propose a new workflow for the annotation of lipidomics and metabolomics LC\u2013MS AIF datasets based on pseudo-MS/MS reconstruction and matching of the fragment ions to fragment databases. The workflow has been implemented as an open-source R package MetaboAnnotatoR",
      "asbval:note": "MetaboAnnotatoR is confirmed as the primary tool used for automated annotation of AIF LC-MS data, including the feature 468.309 m/z shown in Figure 2.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MetaboAnnotatoR",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
