      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card describes a library-entry generation function ('genFragEntry') that does not appear to exist in the paper or is not documented in the provided passages.",
        "The paper focuses on the annotation workflow (using pre-built libraries) rather than on the process of generating library entries from raw MS/MS spectra.",
        "The card's research question implies a detailed algorithmic description of library entry generation, but the paper only briefly mentions that libraries were 'generated from experimental CID MS/MS spectra' without providing function-level documentation.",
        "The card appears to conflate the annotation scoring system (which uses occurrence scores) with library entry generation; these are separate processes in the paper."
      ],
