    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_1c03032__task_005/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The matches for each target feature are compiled and output to a table (.csv) and graphical outputs are saved as .pdf files. For each target feature, a list of the candidates ranked by score is produced, which includes the metabolite name, m/z matched, m/z error (ppm), the number of matched fragments, and score. Additionally, a list containing all rank 1 annotations is produced for quick result inspection. Graphical outputs contain, for each ranked result, the pseudo-MS/MS spectrum comprising the matched peaks and the corresponding EICs; and for each target feature, the pseudo-MS/MS and pseudo-MS (MS1 spectrum containing all ions correlated to the target feature) spectra and the corresponding EICs are stored for later inspection.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes output as CSV tables and PDF graphical outputs. No mention of MGF format output or 'file audit report' in passages. The paper confirms: (1) global results table (.csv), (2) ranked results (.csv), (3) ranked spectra PDFs. MGF format and audit report are not mentioned in provided passages.",
