    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/annotation-candidate-comparative-scoring/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow was designed for feature-by-feature annotation on one or more LC\u2013MS AIF samples... The workflow can be divided into seven steps... (1)Data input. The workflow starts with a table of features (m/z and RT values) to be annotated (target features)... A random selection of 100 LC\u2013MS AIF chromatograms from both Lipid+ and Lipid\u2013 as well as HILIC+ datasets from the MESA cohort was processed in R using XCMS23 version 3.4.4 and RAMClustR package5 to obtain pseudo-MS/MS spectra",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms XCMS is used for peak-picking and feature detection upstream of MetaboAnnotatoR, but the input to MetaboAnnotatoR is a feature table (m/z and RT values), not directly from XCMS. The paper states MetaboAnnotatoR can accept 'a table of features (m/z and RT values)' or 'raw AIF LC\u2013MS data' or 'a RAMClustR object'\u2014not specifically an XCMS object.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "annotation-candidate-comparative-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms performs peak-picking and feature detection to generate the peak-picked data object required as input to annotateRC",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:42:38.537713+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/annotation-candidate-comparative-scoring/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Two R packages, CAMERA10 and RAMClustR,5 can also be used to reconstruct in-source parent-fragment pseudo-MS/MS spectra... Alternatively, a RAMClustR5 R object containing deconvolved pseudo-MS/MS spectra for the features can also be used as data input.",
      "asbval:note": "RAMClustR is confirmed as a tool for generating pseudo-MS/MS spectra and its output is accepted as input to MetaboAnnotatoR.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
