    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ionization-mode-annotation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The nonlipid small-molecule library was generated from experimental CID MS/MS spectra from proton or sodium adducts and deprotonated ions corresponding to metabolites commonly found in human biofluids, such as urine and blood serum or plasma deposited in MassBank12 and GNPS13 databases",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that libraries were generated from MassBank and GNPS sources and that ionization mode (positive/negative) is tracked in library organization ('Positive and negative ionization modes for the same chromatography are analyzed separately, to make effective use of mode-specific reference libraries' \u2014 passage 4). However, the paper does not describe an automated .msp-to-CSV conversion function or tool. Library preparation is described qualitatively but not as a programmatic conversion workflow with mode-annotation suffixes.",
