    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-annotation-result-export/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The matches for each target feature are compiled and output to a table (.csv) and graphical outputs are saved as .pdf files. For each target feature, a list of the candidates ranked by score is produced, which includes the metabolite name, m/z matched, m/z error (ppm), the number of matched fragments, and score. Additionally, a list containing all rank 1 annotations is produced for quick result inspection. Graphical outputs contain, for each ranked result, the pseudo-MS/MS spectrum comprising the matched peaks and the corresponding EICs",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms export of .csv tables, ranked results, and .pdf graphical outputs. However, no mention of MGF (mascot generic format) export for pseudo-MS/MS spectra found in passages. The paper describes PDF outputs but not MGF format specifically.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-annotation-result-export",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
