    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-identifier-mapping-to-lipids/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow was designed for feature-by-feature annotation on one or more LC\u2013MS AIF samples... The workflow can be divided into seven steps... (6)Candidate scoring and ranking. The score indicating the quality of the match between a library candidate and a target feature is composed of two parts: one measuring the similarity in m/z between the target and candidate and one gauging the similarity of the fragmentation patterns",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MetaboAnnotatoR workflow for AIF annotation with fragment matching and scoring, but does NOT name a function called 'annotateRC'. The paper mentions RAMClustR objects as input but does not document an 'annotateRC' function. The core workflow (fragment matching, ranking, lipid annotation) is present, but the specific function name appears to be an extractor error or conflation with RAMClustR.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-identifier-mapping-to-lipids",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Annotate LC-MS All-ion fragmentation features to lipid identities by matching fragment ion patterns against LipidPos ion fragment libraries using the annotateRC function.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:45:18.420754+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-identifier-mapping-to-lipids/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The lipid libraries were adapted from those of the LipidMatch R package,19 which is a library of theoretical m/z values for experimentally observed lipid fragments... Overall, 90,425 lipid entries, comprising several combinations of adducts, observed in both positive and negative modes of ionization were included in the library.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses lipid fragment libraries adapted from LipidMatch, not a library explicitly named 'LipidPos'. The paper does not use the term 'LipidPos' anywhere. The library is organized by adduct and ionization mode (positive/negative) but is not branded as 'LipidPos'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-identifier-mapping-to-lipids",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "matching fragment ion patterns against LipidPos ion fragment libraries",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:45:18.420754+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-identifier-mapping-to-lipids/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow has been implemented as an open-source R package MetaboAnnotatoR, providing tools for automated annotation, reporting, and visualization.",
      "asbval:note": "MetaboAnnotatoR is confirmed as the primary tool in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
