    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-data-output-formatting/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The matches for each target feature are compiled and output to a table (.csv) and graphical outputs are saved as .pdf files. For each target feature, a list of the candidates ranked by score is produced, which includes the metabolite name, m/z matched, m/z error (ppm), the number of matched fragments, and score. Additionally, a list containing all rank 1 annotations is produced for quick result inspection. Graphical outputs contain, for each ranked result, the pseudo-MS/MS spectrum comprising the matched peaks and the corresponding EICs",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms export of .csv tables, .pdf graphical outputs with ranked candidates and pseudo-MS/MS spectra. However, no mention of MGF file export format found in passages. Paper describes CSV and PDF outputs but MGF export is not explicitly documented.",
