    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms-ms-spectrum-peak-annotation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "each parent and fragment in the library is given an occurrence score (s, Figure 1). These scores reflect the likelihood of observing the fragment and allow the user to include metabolites in the library whose fragmentation can only be predicted in silico or obtained from the literature. The match score Sma is then the sum of occurrence scores for all fragments which match pseudo-MS/MS",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes occurrence-based scoring for matched fragments in the MetaboAnnotatoR workflow, but the card's claim about 'applying noise and marker peak thresholds' to annotate raw MS/MS spectra is not explicitly described. The paper focuses on scoring already-identified pseudo-MS/MS peaks against library candidates, not on the upstream task of peak-picking and threshold application to raw spectra. The card appears to describe a hypothetical 'genFragEntry' function that is not mentioned in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms-ms-spectrum-peak-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Annotate fragment peaks in an MS/MS spectrum by applying noise and marker peak thresholds, then scoring matched ions against a metabolite library using occurrence-based scoring.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:45:52.139969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms-ms-spectrum-peak-annotation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes MetaboAnnotatoR extensively but does not mention a function called 'genFragEntry'. The paper describes the workflow steps (pseudo-MS/MS generation, isotopologue check, candidate selection, spectral match, candidate scoring and ranking, output) but does not name a specific function for annotating raw MS/MS spectra with thresholds and occurrence scores. The occurrence scoring is applied to library entries, not to raw spectra via a named function.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms-ms-spectrum-peak-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MetaboAnnotatoR - Provides the genFragEntry function for MS/MS spectrum peak annotation and occurrence scoring",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:45:52.139969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms-ms-spectrum-peak-annotation/002",
