      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A random selection of 100 LC\u2013MS AIF chromatograms from both Lipid+ and Lipid\u2013 as well as HILIC+ datasets from the MESA cohort was processed in R using XCMS version 3.4.4 and RAMClustR package to obtain pseudo-MS/MS spectra (dataset-wide reconstruction)",
      "asbval:note": "RAMClustR is confirmed as co-processing tool for pseudo-MS/MS generation. However, the 'noise filtering' step is not explicitly described as a separate preprocessing step in RAMClustR; rather, correlation-based thresholding occurs within MetaboAnnotatoR's workflow.",
