      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/peak-detection-threshold-application/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow was designed for feature-by-feature annotation on one or more LC\u2013MS AIF samples... This is used to load the raw AIF LC\u2013MS data which should be in the vendor-neutral formats mzML or netCDF. Alternatively, a RAMClustR R object containing deconvolved pseudo-MS/MS spectra for the features can also be used as data input... A random selection of 100 LC\u2013MS AIF chromatograms from both Lipid+ and Lipid\u2013 as well as HILIC+ datasets from the MESA cohort was processed in R using XCMS version 3.4.4 and RAMClustR package to obtain pseudo-MS/MS spectra",
      "asbval:note": "XCMS is confirmed as upstream peak-picking tool used in the workflow.",
