      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:46:58.999176+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pseudo-ms-ms-spectra-ranking-and-curation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We demonstrate the workflow in three human serum datasets containing 599 features manually annotated by experts.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates the workflow on 599 features, confirming it handles multiple features. However, the specific function name 'annotateRC' is not mentioned in the paper, and the specific threshold of 'six or more' features is not stated. The paper does not reference a database called 'LipidPos' by that exact name; it references 'lipid libraries' and 'nonlipid metabolite libraries'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pseudo-ms-ms-spectra-ranking-and-curation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill after executing annotateRC to match six or more lipidomics/metabolomics features against ion fragment databases (e.g., LipidPos)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:46:58.999176+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pseudo-ms-ms-spectra-ranking-and-curation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Alternatively, a RAMClustR5 R object containing deconvolved pseudo-MS/MS spectra for the features can also be used as data input... (6)Candidate scoring and ranking. The score indicating the quality of the match between a library candidate and a target feature is composed of two parts: one measuring the similarity in m/z between the target and candidate and one gauging the similarity of the fragmentation patterns",
      "asbval:note": "Confirmed: workflow uses RAMClustR pseudo-MS/MS objects and ranks multiple candidates by fragmentation pattern matching.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pseudo-ms-ms-spectra-ranking-and-curation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "when you have pseudo-MS/MS spectra from RAMClustR objects and need to identify which of multiple candidate annotations best explain each feature's fragmentation pattern",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:46:58.999176+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/pseudo-ms-ms-spectra-ranking-and-curation/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Most of the features are correctly annotated at rank 1 (highest score) in all datasets... A smaller percentage of the features was not annotated in any of the datasets: 14% and 13% in Lipid+, 27% and 16% in Lipid\u2013, and 24% and 15% in HILIC+ dataset for the QC samples and RC object, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that not all features receive annotations (13-27% unannotated), and provides ranked candidates for validation. The specific example '3 out of 6' is illustrative but not explicitly stated in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "pseudo-ms-ms-spectra-ranking-and-curation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it specifically when you expect only a fraction of features (e.g., 3 out of 6) to receive high-confidence lipid or metabolite annotations and require ranked candidates for manual or automated validation.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:46:58.999176+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ranked-result-extraction-and-display/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For each target feature, a list of the candidates ranked by score is produced, which includes the metabolite name, m/z matched, m/z error (ppm), the number of matched fragments, and score. Additionally, a list containing all rank 1 annotations is produced for quick result inspection.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes ranked candidate output and scoring system (step 7 of workflow), but does not name a function called 'annotateRC' or explicitly document extraction of ranked results from an 'annotateRC results object'. The paper describes the MetaboAnnotatoR workflow output structure and ranking, but the specific function name 'annotateRC' and the object structure are not mentioned in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ranked-result-extraction-and-display",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Extract and display ranked candidate metabolite annotations for a specific LC\u2013MS feature from the annotateRC results object, preserving annotation scores and rank order.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:47:18.777257+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ranked-result-extraction-and-display/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The outputs from Figure 2 allow the analyst to evaluate the quality of the annotation and decide on its confidence. [...] For each ranked result, the pseudo-MS/MS spectrum comprising the matched peaks and the corresponding EICs; and for each target feature, the pseudo-MS/MS and pseudo-MS (MS1 spectrum containing all ions correlated to the target feature) spectra and the corresponding EICs are stored for later inspection.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly supports the use case of inspecting ranked results and alternative annotations for quality evaluation and confidence assessment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ranked-result-extraction-and-display",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill enables inspection of alternative candidate annotations beyond the top-ranked hit, critical for understanding annotation ambiguity and lipid isomer/isobar confusion in untargeted AIF metabolomics.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:47:18.777257+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ranked-result-extraction-and-display/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow is designed to annotate features including isotopologue peaks, adducts, and in-source fragments. [...] For each target feature, a list of the candidates ranked by score is produced, which includes the metabolite name, m/z matched, m/z error (ppm), the number of matched fragments, and score.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper supports the use case of examining multiple candidate annotations for features with potential ambiguity.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
