      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-library-entry-generation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The nonlipid small-molecule library was generated from experimental CID MS/MS spectra from proton or sodium adducts and deprotonated ions corresponding to metabolites commonly found in human biofluids, such as urine and blood serum or plasma deposited in MassBank12 and GNPS13 databases",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that libraries are built from MassBank and GNPS spectra, but does not provide a detailed workflow or function for converting individual spectra into scored library entries. The paper describes the *result* (library structure) but not the *process* of entry generation.",
