    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-library-format-conversion/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow is freely available as an open-source R package, MetaboAnnotatoR, together with the fragment libraries from Github (https://github.com/gggraca/MetaboAnnotatoR)... The libraries can be customized by the user, for instance, by importing external libraries as .txt and .msp files.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MetaboAnnotatoR accepts .msp files as input and supports custom library import, but does not describe or name a specific 'mspToLib' conversion function. The card claims a specific conversion workflow/function that is not explicitly named or detailed in the paper. The paper states libraries 'can be customized by the user, for instance, by importing external libraries as .txt and .msp files' but does not detail the conversion mechanism or CSV output format with ionization mode suffixes.",
