      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The libraries can be customized by the user, for instance, by importing external libraries as .txt and .msp files... The libraries include both lipids and small-molecule (nonlipid) metabolites... organized as a collection of .csv files, one for each combination of a metabolite or class of metabolites (lipids) and an adducting species",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that MetaboAnnotatoR libraries are organized as CSV files with ionization mode organization (positive/negative), and that .msp files can be imported. However, the paper does not explicitly describe a conversion function or workflow that transforms .msp to CSV with ionization mode suffixes. The organization described is the target format, but the conversion mechanism is not detailed.",
