      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow was designed for feature-by-feature annotation on one or more LC\u2013MS AIF samples... The workflow can be divided into seven steps... (1)Data input. The workflow starts with a table of features (m/z and RT values) to be annotated (target features)... A random selection of 100 LC\u2013MS AIF chromatograms from both Lipid+ and Lipid\u2013 as well as HILIC+ datasets from the MESA cohort was processed in R using XCMS version 3.4.4 and RAMClustR package to obtain pseudo-MS/MS spectra",
