    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow can be divided into seven steps detailed below: (1)Data input. The workflow starts with a table of features (m/z and RT values) to be annotated (target features) and samples where the target features have been detected. This is used to load the raw AIF LC\u2013MS data which should be in the vendor-neutral formats mzML or netCDF. Alternatively, a RAMClustR5 R object containing deconvolved pseudo-MS/MS spectra for the features can also be used as data input.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes RAMClustR object as alternative input to MetaboAnnotatoR workflow, confirming the integration bridges feature detection and annotation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill bridges feature detection and spectral clustering, enabling downstream annotation workflows in untargeted LC-MS all-ion fragmentation metabolomics.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:32.264881+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Untargeted metabolomics and lipidomics LC-MS experiments produce complex datasets, usually containing tens of thousands of features from thousands of metabolites whose annotation requires additional MS/MS experiments and expert knowledge. All-ion fragmentation (AIF) LC-MS/MS acquisition provides fragmentation data at no additional experimental time cost.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes AIF as the acquisition mode and fragment matching as the annotation approach.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have raw LC-MS all-ion fragmentation (AIF) chromatograms in centroid mode and need to prepare them for metabolite annotation using fragment ion matching.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:32.264881+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Alternatively, a RAMClustR5 R object containing deconvolved pseudo-MS/MS spectra for the features can also be used as data input.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms RAMClustR object can be used as input to MetaboAnnotatoR, but does not explicitly name a function called 'annotateRC'. The paper describes the workflow as a general 7-step process, not a specific function name. The function name 'annotateRC' appears to be inferred by the extractor but is not verbatim in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "you have processed your data through xcms for peak detection and RamClustR for pseudo-MS/MS spectrum generation, and you need to combine these two objects into a single analytical framework before applying the annotateRC function.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:32.264881+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A random selection of 100 LC\u2013MS AIF chromatograms from both Lipid+ and Lipid\u2013 as well as HILIC+ datasets from the MESA cohort was processed in R using XCMS23 version 3.4.4 and RAMClustR package5 to obtain pseudo-MS/MS spectra",
      "asbval:note": "XCMS is confirmed as the peak detection tool used in the workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms - Peak detection and feature alignment from raw LC-MS chromatograms; produces xcms object with m/z and intensity matrices",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:32.264881+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Two R packages, CAMERA10 and RAMClustR,5 can also be used to reconstruct in-source parent-fragment pseudo-MS/MS spectra.",
      "asbval:note": "RAMClustR is confirmed for pseudo-MS/MS spectrum generation from AIF data.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "RamClustR - Clustering of co-eluting ions and generation of pseudo-MS/MS spectra from all-ion fragmentation data; produces RC object with fragment ion arrays",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:32.264881+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Alternatively, a RAMClustR5 R object containing deconvolved pseudo-MS/MS spectra for the features can also be used as data input.",
      "asbval:note": "MetaboAnnotatoR is confirmed as the annotation tool that accepts RAMClustR objects, but the specific function name 'annotateRC' is not mentioned in the paper. The paper describes the workflow generically without naming individual functions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03032",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-ramclustr-data-object-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MetaboAnnotatoR - Fragment-based metabolite annotation function (annotateRC) that consumes integrated xcms and RamClustR objects and matches fragments against ion libraries",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:32.264881+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
